  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into legitimate economic channels\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most criminal codes require:\n- Intent to disguise the origin of funds\n- Knowledge that money comes from illegal activities\n- Deliberate attempts to hide the money's source\n\nWould you like me to provide more specific details about money laundering laws?",
